Sony has partnered with Seagate to launch an officially-licensed Game Drive for PlayStation 4 consoles. This 2TB external hard drive allows gamers to boost their PS4’s storage capacity, and connects via a USB cable to the console. “Our new Game Drive for PS4 has been rigorously tested and is optimized for PS4 systems,” Sony said. “The large increase in storage capacity lets you hang on to your favorite older titles and add-ons while still leaving room for new games.” It should be noted that the games loaded onto the 2TB Game Drive can only be accessed by the account which transferred the content. Sony said the external hard drive is easy to set up, can hold around 50 games, and is just as fast as playing titles from the PS4’s internal storage. The Game Drive for will be available for a recommended retail price of $90.  